cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.SI. 

The paper presents an algorithm for computing a cycle separator in a planar graph, which is a problem related to graph theory and computational geometry. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves some graph theoretic concepts, such as layered decomposition, which suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper may be relevant to researchers working on graph partitioning and network analysis, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
